g.text: 1) Data Selection - Import MRI features and cognitive scores from separate files. Select the specific columns needed from each dataset.
2) Combine Datasets - Merge the selected MRI features and cognitive scores into a single dataset for analysis.
3) Data Preprocessing - Handle any missing values in the combined data. Split the dataset into training and testing sets.
4) Train Model - Train a Random Forest machine learning model using the training data.
5) Testing and Evaluation - Test the trained model on the unseen test data. Evaluate its performance using metrics like confusion matrix and ROC analysis.
6) Feature Exploration - Explore the trained model to understand how it makes predictions and identify the most important features.
